# Git commit discipline

After each **major change** in Quest Soaring, create a git commit before moving on.

## What counts as major

- New system or milestone (physics, terrain, VR input, weather, tests)
- New scene, prefab, or test assembly
- Refactor touching multiple scripts or project settings
- Bug fix that changes gameplay or test behavior

## What does NOT need its own commit

- Typo in comment, formatting-only edits
- WIP within the same feature (squash into one commit when done)

## Commit message style

Use imperative mood, one line summary + optional body:

```
Add glider aerodynamics model and EditMode tests

Heuristic lift/drag/stall based on AoA and airspeed.
```

## Workflow

1. Finish a logical unit of work
2. Run EditMode tests when scripts changed
3. `git add` relevant files only (never `.env`, `Library/`, `UserSettings/`)
4. Commit with descriptive message
5. Push when remote exists and user asks or at end of session milestone
